    "itinerary": "Day 1 / 20.7. Ulaanbaatar - Elsen Tasarkhai <br> In the morning our team will meet with you at your hotel, and together you will drive towards Kharkhorin. On the way you will stop by notification Tasarkhai 80 km long dunes, surrounded by woody hills and wide steep. Here you will have a great opportunity to try a camel riding, and explore the area. The Day 2 / 7.21. Elsen Tasarkhai - Kharkhorin - Bat - Olzii <br> In the morning you will leave the sand dunes and drive to Kharkhorin, Where You Will visit Erdene Zuu monastery, and a stone turtle located nearby, The Last Remnant of ancient Karakorum. From Kharkhorin You Will Drive Further to the Bat - Olzii, a small village located at the bank of Orkhon River. The Day 3 / 7.22. Mongolian Felt Festival <br> Today You Will Participate in one being a local Felt festival. The festival will give you a great opportunity to observing the nomadic traditional technology of making wrong Such as combing, laying out, and dragging wrong with a horse. In the afternoon you will go for a ride to visit Ulaan Tsutgalan, a famous ten meters wide and twenty meter high waterfall, located in the middle of Orkhon valley. The Day 4 / 7.23. Yak Festival <br> Today You Will Participate In another local event - Yak Festival. The festival will start with a yak races. Then a yak lassoing competition will take place and a yak polo game. In the evening you will go for a horse ride along the banks of Orkhon River. The Day 5 / 24.07. Bat - Olzii - Khustai National Park Photos Early in the morning you will leave the Bat - Olzii and drive in the direction of Ulaanbaatar. You will pass Kharkhorin, Elsen Tasarkhai and stop in Khustain National Park, a place famous for its growing population of rare Przewalski's horses. <br> Day 6 / 25.07. Khustai National Park - Ulaanbaatar <br> In the morning you will explore the park and search for Przewalski's horses. Later you will drive back to Ulaanbaatar.",
